Documents
A document is the smallest unit that can be tracked by a workflow. For example, a document can be a set of pages that make up one bill, one
statement, or one mailpiece.
A print file can contain thousands of documents. If the print file is in AFP format, each document is bounded by the Begin Page Group and End
Page Group AFP structured fields.
